HEADWORD: Puisny
<hw>Puis"ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Puisne; younger;
inferior; petty; unskilled.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>puisny</qex> tilter, that spurs his horse but on one
